The paper also involves optimization techniques for matching sequences, which suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves graph algorithms for matching sequences, which suggests the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of training sequences for matching, which suggests the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of error exponents, which suggests the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
